&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;statahead thread stack:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
# cat stack
[&amp;lt;0&amp;gt;] ll_statahead_thread+0x2fd/0x1b20 [lustre]
[&amp;lt;0&amp;gt;] kthread+0x127/0x150
[&amp;lt;0&amp;gt;] ret_from_fork+0x1f/0x30&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A similar problem is fixed here - &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-15660&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-15660&lt;/a&gt; . However, that is fixed in the client version used 2.15.5 &lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Environment:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
Lustre client, Kubernetes environment.&#160;
Ubuntu client 22.04 with kernel version 5.15.0-1045
Lustre mounted via CSI driver
&#160; &lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Since it is a Kubernetes environment, there is a need to mount and unmount the Lustre file system every time the container starts on the worker node. When the above problem happens, the node becomes unavailable for any containers to be started taking it offline until the node is rebooted.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Lustre client, Kubernetes environment. &lt;br/&gt;
